description.narrative: By end 2015, targeted key institutions provide improved quality health services to a greater number of children, which contributes to Child Health, Early Childhood Development, Immunization, Maternal And Newborn Health, Prevention Of Stunting And Other Forms Of Malnutrition, Treatment Of Severe Acute Malnutrition. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Evaluations, Research And Data, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By end 2015, more children and youth, and especially the most vulnera ble, benefit from equitable improvements in the key sectors defined by t he Kosovo Midterm Expenditure Framework
